<paragraph id="E5225549F6D12E66861F85116BDCEE37" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Typification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9453AD6FB21F395207E5E1F1AA5481AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">There appears to be no syntype at Madrid so we have selected the specimen at OXF as the lectotype as this is a more complete specimen than that at Paris.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5244AA02F01CBA3F1DA75E2BC198EECE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="3DB62E491FC2522DB6B645949BAC6979" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A6265A447BA61F6B9D74623B7D86D74D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distinct because of the relatively large sepals with long erect awn-like mucros. The capsule is very unusual, being often pubescent. The short, angled or winged pedicels are also noteworthy.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
